keyFacts: A multi-agency briefing call on the Epstein case was scheduled for October 20, 2020.
The call was organized by the FBI and included attendees from the Office of the Deputy Attorney General (ODAG), Justice Management Division (JMD), and Civil Rights Division (CRT).
The New York FBI field office was also listed as an attendee, indicating ongoing investigative coordination.
The calendar entry is classified as 'X-PERSONAL' and was created and modified in October 2020.
The document itself is a metadata-rich calendar entry, not a transcript of the meeting's content.
